		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/25/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 01:55:48</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=3651"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=3651')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=43596&amp;TOPIC_ID=5399&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Question+on+meditation%2E&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I remember reading something that VI posted which stated that +skill items will not take you over the max cap.  Also, the number 255 is a software cap. (Could be argued that it's a hardware thing too I guess, but let's not get into semantics.)</P><P>The variable that stores your str/int/meditation/baking is a byte, which = 2^8 = 256.  Since 0 is a possible value, the range goes from 0-255.  This is where some people claim that if you get uber resists, it actually rolls back down, ie, a value of 257 would put you at 1 again.  Simple code fix really for Verant to do, just a matter of finding all the instances in their bloated, mud based server :)</P><P>Personally, I've never seen any of my stats or resists show a value greater than 255.  If anyone has seen this, then the only explanation I can come up with is that in your player file, the value is stored as a byte but displayed on the client as an integer, which can go as high as 32767 before rolling back over (to -32768 this time).  Has anyone ever seen any of their stats go over 255 with buffs and mana songs?  Always wondered about this.</P><P>Anyways, that was my sudden geek outburst of the day, if this made any sense to anyone, Innoruuk have mercy on your soul.</P><P>Morwenn</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
